1	# Trackgentic Library ‚Äî Data Model & Types
2	
3	All types are defined in `src/types/`. This document specifies every type, interface, and file format.
4	
5	## 1. Issue Status
6	
7	```typescript
8	type IssueStatus = "idea" | "todo" | "in-progress" | "done" | "closed";
9	```
10	
11	Status progression: `idea -> todo -> in-progress -> done -> closed`
12	
13	The special filter value `"open"` is **not** a real status ‚Äî it means "all statuses except `closed`".
14	
15	## 2. Issue ID
16	
17	```typescript
18	type IssueId = string; // 10 chars: 6 from timestamp base36 + 4 random base36
19	```
20	
21	Generation: `Date.now().toString(36).slice(0, 6) + Math.random().toString(36).slice(-4)`
22	
23	IDs are sortable by creation time.
24	
25	## 3. Comment ID
26	
27	```typescript
28	type CommentId = string; // Same format as IssueId: 10-char base36
29	```
30	
31	Generated with the same algorithm as issue IDs.
32	
33	## 4. Event Types
34	
35	### Event (base shape)
36	
37	```typescript
38	interface BaseEvent {
39	  timestamp: string; // ISO 8601
40	  author: string;    // resolved user name or "system"
41	}
42	```
43	
44	### Typed events
45	
46	```typescript
47	type Event =
48	  | CreationEvent
49	  | UpdateEvent
50	  | CommentEvent
51	  | CommentUpdateEvent
52	  | CommentDeleteEvent
53	  | BlockageAddedEvent
54	  | BlockageResolvedEvent
55	  | BlockageDeletedEvent;
56	
57	interface CreationEvent extends BaseEvent {
58	  type: "creation";
59	  // No content ‚Äî creation is just a marker
60	}
61	
62	interface UpdateEvent extends BaseEvent {
63	  type: "update";
64	  content: Partial<Pick<IssueProperties, "title" | "description" | "status" | "assignee" | "tags" | "priority" | "parentId">> & {
65	    reason?: string; // for system auto-promotion events
66	  };
67	}
68	
69	interface CommentEvent extends BaseEvent {
70	  type: "comment";
71	  content: {
72	    id: CommentId;
73	    content: string;
74	  };
75	}
76	
77	interface CommentUpdateEvent extends BaseEvent {
78	  type: "comment-update";
79	  content: {
80	    id: CommentId;
81	    content: string;
82	  };
83	}
84	
85	interface CommentDeleteEvent extends BaseEvent {
86	  type: "comment-delete";
87	  content: {
88	    id: CommentId;
89	  };
90	}
91	
92	interface BlockageAddedEvent extends BaseEvent {
93	  type: "blockage-added";
94	  content: {
95	    blockerId: IssueId;
96	  };
97	}
98	
99	interface BlockageResolvedEvent extends BaseEvent {
100	  type: "blockage-resolved";
101	  content: {
102	    blockerId: IssueId;
103	  };
104	}
105	
106	interface BlockageDeletedEvent extends BaseEvent {
107	  type: "blockage-deleted";
108	  content: {
109	    blockerId: IssueId;
110	  };
111	}
112	```
113	
114	## 5. Issue Properties
115	
116	These are the mutable properties of an issue, reconstructed by replaying events.
117	
118	```typescript
119	interface IssueProperties {
120	  id: IssueId;
121	  title: string;
122	  description: string;
123	  status: IssueStatus;
124	  assignee: string | null;
125	  parentId: IssueId | null;
126	  tags: string[];
127	  priority: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5;
128	}
129	```
130	
131	## 6. Computed Issue (view output)
132	
133	The full computed state of an issue, including computed fields.
134	
135	```typescript
136	interface ComputedIssue extends IssueProperties {
137	  createdAt: string;   // ISO 8601 ‚Äî timestamp of creation event
138	  createdBy: string;   // author of creation event
139	  updatedAt: string;   // ISO 8601 ‚Äî timestamp of last event
140	}
141	```
142	
143	## 7. Comment (computed)
144	
145	```typescript
146	interface ComputedComment {
147	  id: CommentId;
148	  author: string;
149	  content: string;
150	  timestamp: string;    // ISO 8601 ‚Äî when the comment was created
151	  editedAt: string | null; // ISO 8601 ‚Äî when last comment-update was applied, or null
152	}
153	```
154	
155	## 8. Index File (`index.json`)
156	
157	```typescript
158	interface IndexFile {
159	  open: IndexEntry[];       // Issues with status !== "closed", sorted by id
160	  closed: IndexEntry[];     // Issues with status === "closed", sorted by id
161	  childrenOf: Record<IssueId, IssueId[]>; // parentId -> child IDs
162	}
163	
164	interface IndexEntry {
165	  id: IssueId;
166	  title: string;
167	  path: string;             // relative path to issue file
168	  status: IssueStatus;
169	  assignee: string | null;
170	  parentId: IssueId | null;
171	  tags: string[];
172	  priority: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5;
173	}
174	```
175	
176	### Invariants
177	
178	- Both arrays are **sorted by issue id** (which is time-sortable).
179	- `open` contains entries where `status !== "closed"`.
180	- `closed` contains entries where `status === "closed"`.
181	- When status changes to/from `closed`, the entry moves between arrays.
182	- `childrenOf` keys only exist for issues that have children. Absent key = no children.
183	
184	## 9. Config File (`config.json`)
185	
186	```typescript
187	interface ConfigFile {
188	  auth: {
189	    mode: "open" | "read-only" | "strict";
190	    defaultUser: string;
191	  };
192	}
193	```
194	
195	Defaults on `init`:
196	```json
197	{
198	  "auth": {
199	    "mode": "read-only",
200	    "defaultUser": "anonymous"
201	  }
202	}
203	```
204	
205	## 10. Dependencies File (`dependencies.json`)
206	
207	```typescript
208	interface DependenciesFile {
209	  blockedBy: Record<IssueId, BlockageEntry[]>; // what blocks me
210	  blocks: Record<IssueId, BlockageEntry[]>;    // what I block
211	}
212	
213	interface BlockageEntry {
214	  blockerId: IssueId;
215	  blockedId: IssueId;
216	  status: "active" | "resolved";
217	}
218	```
219	
220	### Invariant
221	
222	Both maps are **always in sync**. Every mutation writes both sides atomically.
223	
224	## 11. Users File (`users.json`)
225	
226	```typescript
227	interface UsersFile {
228	  users: UserEntry[];
229	}
230	
231	interface UserEntry {
232	  name: string;           // stored lowercase
233	  token: string;          // format: tk_ + 8 random alphanumeric chars
234	  registeredAt: string;   // ISO 8601
235	}
236	```
237	
238	## 12. Issue Event File (`issues/[id].json`)
239	
240	```typescript
241	type IssueEventFile = Event[]; // append-only array of events
242	```
243	
244	## 13. Initial File Contents on `init`
245	
246	### `index.json`
247	```json
248	{
249	  "open": [],
250	  "closed": [],
251	  "childrenOf": {}
252	}
253	```
254	
255	### `dependencies.json`
256	```json
257	{
258	  "blockedBy": {},
259	  "blocks": {}
260	}
261	```
262	
263	### `users.json`
264	```json
265	{
266	  "users": []
267	}
268	```
269	
270	## 14. Blockage Info (view output)
271	
272	```typescript
273	interface BlockageInfo {
274	  issueId: IssueId;
275	  blockedBy: BlockageEntry[];
276	  blocks: BlockageEntry[];
277	}
278	```
279	
280	## 15. User Info (list output)
281	
282	```typescript
283	interface UserInfo {
284	  name: string;
285	  registeredAt: string;
286	}
287	```
